OL,3,CCumbria Police see increase in hate
OL,4,Ccrime and knife crime in annual figures
OL,6,FThe force said they had some "of the
OL,7,Fbest" results for anti-social
OL,8,Fbehaviour in the country, which they
OL,9,Fsay is thanks to Operation Enhance -
OL,10,Ffunding they received last year from
OL,11,Fthe government to increase foot
OL,12,Fpatrols.
OL,14,FIt led to an overall drop of 28.6% in
OL,15,FCumberland and a 38% drop in
OL,16,FWestmorland and Furness.
OL,18,FIn the current financial year (2026-
OL,19,F7), Cumbria Police no longer receives
OL,20,Fgovernment support to pay for
OL,21,FOperation Enhance
OL,26,@nD@^OUoD@EO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,322,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F321A1781884084
OL,3,CCumbria Police see increase in hate
OL,4,Ccrime and knife crime in annual figures
OL,6,F"Yes, the funding has stopped. That
OL,7,Fdoesn't mean that the police and my
OL,8,Foffice are going to stop targeting
OL,9,Fareas where we know there's antisocial
OL,10,Fbehaviour," David Allen explains.
OL,12,F"Myself and the Chief Constable have
OL,13,Ftaken the decision to continue and
OL,14,Fcarry on with funding in those hotspot
OL,15,Fareas.
OL,17,F"There will be additional police
OL,18,Fpatrols to make sure that we do not
OL,19,Fsee an increase in anti-social
OL,20,Fbehaviour, having driven it down so
OL,21,Fsubstantially."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@KO]tD@AOUyD@AOU}D@OO]
